The Sanga Local Government Council in Kaduna State has presented a deep freezer and power generating set to the Primary Health Care Department (PHC) of the council to boost its services Mr Charles Danladi, the Chairman of the Council, who presented the items Saturday to the PHC Director, Mrs Martha Nom, said the gesture was to enhance quality healthcare delivery. “The deep freezer and the power generating set will guarantee the preservation of especially vaccines and other essential drugs in the event of power outage from the public source. “I hope the department will handle the items well and use them for the intended purpose,” he said. Responding, Nom appreciated the Council for the gesture and said it was “heartwarming”. She commended the responsive disposition of the chairman to the challenges of the people of the area.